From: Chenghao Duan <duanchenghao@kylinos.cn>
Date: Thu, 19 Mar 2026 09:28:45 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] mm/memfd_luo: use i_size_write() to set inode size during
 retrieve

Use i_size_write() instead of directly assigning to inode->i_size when
restoring the memfd size in memfd_luo_retrieve().

No functional change intended.

Link: https://lkml.kernel.org/r/20260319012845.29570-4-duanchenghao@kylinos.cn
Signed-off-by: Chenghao Duan <duanchenghao@kylinos.cn>
Reviewed-by: Pasha Tatashin <pasha.tatashin@soleen.com>
Cc: Haoran Jiang <jianghaoran@kylinos.cn>
Cc: Mike Rapoport <rppt@kernel.org>
Cc: Pratyush Yadav <pratyush@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
---
 mm/memfd_luo.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mm/memfd_luo.c b/mm/memfd_luo.c
index a0b8fdaef2031..6fc47502c83ba 100644
--- a/mm/memfd_luo.c
+++ b/mm/memfd_luo.c
@@ -531,7 +531,7 @@ static int memfd_luo_retrieve(struct liveupdate_file_op_args *args)
 	}
 
 	vfs_setpos(file, ser->pos, MAX_LFS_FILESIZE);
-	file->f_inode->i_size = ser->size;
+	i_size_write(file_inode(file), ser->size);
 
 	if (ser->nr_folios) {
 		folios_ser = kho_restore_vmalloc(&ser->folios);
-- 
2.47.3

